%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22My%2029-year-old%20son%20had%20a%20stomach%20ache%20that%20wouldn't%20go%20away.%20He%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20stage%204%20colon%20cancer%20and%20died%208%20months%20later.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Andrew%20Reaster%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a075f2a94eb4c909fb2cffa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAndrew%20Reaster%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20stage%204%20colon%20cancer%20in%20January%202025%20after%20a%20prolonged%20stomach%20ache.%3Cp%3EKathy%20Lemoine%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAndrew%20Reaster%2C%20a%2029-year-old%20UPS%20driver%20in%20Georgia%2C%20had%20a%20sudden%20three-day-long%20stomach%20ache.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20%3Ca%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprevent-colon-cancer-how-to-tell-poop-is-normal-doctor-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estage%204%20colon%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20died%20eight%20months%20later.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHis%20mother%2C%20Kathy%20Lemoine%2C%20wants%20more%20young%20people%20and%20parents%20to%20know%20the%20risks%20of%20colon%20cancer.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Kathy%20Lemoine%2C%2058%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Lawrenceville%2C%20Georgia.%20Her%20son%2C%20Andrew%20Reaster%2C%20died%20on%20August%209%2C%202025%2C%20from%20colon%20cancer.%20This%20story%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20son%20Andrew%20lived%20life%20to%20the%20fullest%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20a%20kid%20at%20heart%2C%20decorating%20his%20condo%20with%20Pok%C3%A9mon%20and%20Legos.%20He%20loved%20his%20job%20as%20a%20UPS%20driver%2C%20and%20many%20of%20his%20customers%20loved%20him.%20He%20would%20jump%20around%20and%20pet%20their%20dogs.%20It%20seemed%20that%20each%20friend%20he%20had%20considered%20him%20their%20best%20friend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20top%20of%20his%20active%20job%2C%20Andrew%20was%20also%20very%20regimented%20about%20his%20health.%20He%20followed%20a%20mostly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-environmental-causes-microplastics-antibiotics-sleep-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclean%20diet%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20never%20skipped%20his%20dental%20appointments.%20He%20also%20had%20perfect%20school%20attendance%20and%20was%20rarely%20sick.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20when%20he%20called%20me%20in%20January%202025%20about%20a%20stomach%20ache%20that%20wouldn't%20go%20away%20for%20three%20days%2C%20I%20immediately%20called%20a%20gastroenterologist%20in%20my%20town.%20Andrew%20came%20in%20the%20next%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20doctor%20immediately%20felt%20something%20hard%20during%20Andrew's%20rectal%20exam%20and%20scheduled%20an%20emergency%20colonoscopy.%20After%20a%20major%20snowstorm%2C%20Andrew%20came%20in%20a%20few%20days%20later.%20I%20went%20with%20him%2C%20thinking%20the%20procedure%20would%20last%20at%20least%20half%20an%20hour.%20Ten%20minutes%20later%2C%20I%20was%20called%20in.%20They%20couldn't%20even%20fit%20the%20scope%20through%20because%20of%20the%20blockage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20a%20week%2C%20we%20learned%20he%20had%20stage%204%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-doctor-22-year-old-symptoms-to-know-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecolon%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20the%20cancer%20spreading%20to%20his%20liver%2C%20lungs%2C%20and%20stomach%20lining.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20when%20our%20nightmare%20began.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2220a29e6c-f4f9-4e66-9871-522827aad2da%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20hardest%20decision%20I%20ever%20had%20to%20make%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22964%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kathy%20Lemoine%20with%20her%20son%20Andrew%20Reaster%20and%20her%20daughter%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a075d1994eb4c909fb2cfd9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22723%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKathy%20Lemoine%20(center)%20with%20Andrew%20and%20her%20daughter%20in%20May%202025.%20This%20is%20the%20last%20photo%20they%20took%20together.%3Cp%3EKathy%20Lemoine%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20learned%20from%20the%20CT%20scans%20that%20the%20mass%20couldn't%20be%20surgically%20removed%20and%20that%20Andrew%20would%20require%20chemotherapy%20treatment%20and%20a%20colostomy%2C%20a%20procedure%20that%20creates%20an%20opening%20in%20his%20abdomen%20to%20collect%20waste%20through%20a%20colostomy%20bag.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20couldn't%20breathe.%20I%20felt%20like%20there%20was%20a%20hand%20squeezing%20my%20heart.%20Because%20Andrew%20had%20Asperger's%2C%20now%20known%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-autism-surprising-facts-about-autism-spectrum-2019-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eautism%20spectrum%20disorder%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20knew%20if%20I%20focused%20on%20the%20negative%2C%20that's%20what%20he%20would%20end%20up%20doing%2C%20too.%20So%20I%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BOK%2C%20honey%2C%20we%20can%20do%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20went%20to%20the%20front%20desk%20to%20start%20the%20paperwork%20for%20short-term%20disability.%20I%20called%20the%20doctor%20over%20and%20asked%20for%20a%20prognosis.%20He%20told%20me%20that%20without%20treatment%2C%20Andrew%20had%20about%20one%20month%20to%20live.%20With%20treatment%2C%20about%20six.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Andrew%20drove%20home%2C%20I%20called%20my%20mom.%20I%20broke%20down%20on%20the%20phone.%20I%20was%20inconsolable.%20I%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20can't%20believe%20that%20my%20son%20is%20dying.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndrew%20worked%20right%20until%20the%20day%20before%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flife-with-a-colostomy-bag-21-year-old-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehis%20colostomy%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20February%202025.%20He%20was%20so%20worried%20about%20getting%20his%20short-term%20disability%20paperwork%20right%20so%20he%20wouldn't%20lose%20his%20job.%20All%20he%20talked%20about%20was%20having%20the%20colostomy%20bag%20removed%20and%20going%20back%20to%20work%20after%20he%20kicked%20cancer's%20butt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20colostomy%20was%20supposed%20to%20involve%20a%20three-%20to%20five-day%20hospital%20stay.%20Due%20to%20complications%2C%20Andrew%20ended%20up%20being%20there%20for%2048%20days.%20He%20had%20fevers%2C%20which%20the%20hospital%20staff%20first%20thought%20were%20infections%20but%20later%20deduced%20were%20caused%20by%20his%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20Andrew%20gave%20me%20power%20of%20attorney%2C%20the%20doctor%20pulled%20me%20aside%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BMom%2C%20you%20have%20a%20huge%20decision%20to%20make.%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-true-hidden-cost-price-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWithout%20chemotherapy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Andrew%20would%20only%20live%20for%20about%20three%20more%20weeks%2C%20but%20given%20how%20weak%20he%20was%2C%20there%20was%20a%20chance%20he%20wouldn't%20make%20it%20through%20the%20night%20if%20we%20started%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20the%20hardest%20decision%20I%20ever%20had%20to%20make.%20I%20knew%20I%20would%20regret%20not%20trying%20chemotherapy.%20I%20sat%20with%20him%20throughout%20the%20three-day%20regimen%2C%20waiting%20to%20see%20what%20happened.%20It%20was%20scary%20because%20I%20could%20have%20lost%20him%20at%20any%20point.%20We%20ended%20up%20watching%20%26quot%3BCars%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BFast%20%26amp%3B%20Furious%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20all%20these%20different%20movies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20made%20it.%20The%20doctor%20was%20shocked.%20I%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%20my%20God%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20kick%20this.%26quot%3B%20Andrew%20came%20back%20for%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdiagnosed-with-colon-cancer-only-had-one-symptom-stomach-pain-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esecond%20round%20of%20chemo%3C%2Fa%3E%20two%20weeks%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229c967371-6c03-4cb4-aed6-bc61196588b1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrying%20to%20stay%20positive%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAndrew%20started%20to%20feel%20a%20little%20bit%20better.%20He%20still%20couldn't%20work%2C%20but%20he%20went%20out%20with%20his%20friends.%20In%20the%20meantime%2C%20a%20new%20doctor%20closer%20to%20Andrew's%20home%20encouraged%20me%20to%20look%20into%20any%20clinical%20trials%20I%20could%20find%20%E2%80%94%20he%20really%20didn't%20think%20Andrew%20had%20very%20long.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20chemo%20became%20harsher%20and%20harsher%20on%20Andrew.%20His%20white%20blood%20cell%20count%20was%20too%20low%20to%20continue%20chemo%2C%20and%20he%20couldn't%20go%20to%20the%20bathroom%2C%20even%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-colon-cancer-misdiagnosed-ibs-hemorrhoid-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecolostomy%20bag%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Still%2C%20he%20seemed%20to%20keep%20a%20positive%20outlook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20he%20turned%2030%20in%20July%202025%2C%20he%20only%20weighed%20140%20pounds%2C%20down%20from%20210.%20Toward%20the%20end%2C%20he%20didn't%20want%20friends%20and%20family%20visiting%20him%20anymore%2C%20seeing%20how%20skeletal%20he'd%20become.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20suffered%20greatly.%20He%20was%20in%20constant%20pain%20until%20he%20died%20on%20August%209%2C%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20hindsight%2C%20I%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%20my%20God%2C%20I%20should%20not%20have%20let%20him%20suffer%20that%20long.%20We%20should%20have%20just%20let%20him%20go.%26quot%3B%20But%20I%20think%20if%20I%20let%20him%20go%2C%20then%20I%20would%20be%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%20my%20gosh%2C%20we%20should%20have%20tried%20harder.%26quot%3B%20So%20no%20matter%20what%2C%20I%20would%20have%20regrets%2C%20which%20I%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20heartbreaking%2C%20watching%20him%20fade%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228748e037-4f57-461e-adf8-35adb5f70709%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20still%20wonder%20if%20we%20missed%20early%20symptoms%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Andrew%20Reaster%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a075cc6abc4e9d88574a89d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAndrew%20had%20no%20family%20history%20of%20colon%20cancer.%3Cp%3EKathy%20Lemoine%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20no%20idea%20that%20colon%20cancer%20was%20something%20to%20look%20out%20for.%20Andrew%20was%20young%2C%20had%20no%20family%20history%2C%20and%20never%20had%20any%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-misdiagnosis-young-people-ibs-gluten-allergy-symptoms-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edigestive%20issues%3C%2Fa%3E%20other%20than%20that%20stomach%20ache.%20I%20believe%20that%20he%20probably%20had%20little%20signs%20here%20and%20there%2C%20but%20just%20didn't%20know%20or%20dismissed%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColon%20cancer%20is%20now%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-leading-cause-cancer-death-under-50-shocking-experts-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeadliest%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20people%20under%2050.%20It's%20also%20very%20treatable%20if%20caught%20early.%20I%20want%20people%20under%2045%20to%20know%20all%20the%20risks%2C%20so%20they%20can%20get%20screened%20the%20moment%20they%20notice%20any%20warning%20signs%2C%20whether%20they%20get%20colonoscopies%20or%20at-home%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feasy-at-home-colon-cancer-screening-tests-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecolon%20cancer%20tests%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20think%20people%20strugg