3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERob%20Mallernee%20has%20worked%20with%20ultra-high-net-worth%20families%20for%20more%20than%2030%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20said%20the%20richest%20families%20tend%20to%20maintain%20their%20wealth%20with%20four%20habits.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EInstilling%20purpose%20in%20the%20next%20generation%20and%20being%20frugal%20are%20key%20to%20preserving%20wealth%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Rob%20Mallernee%2C%2050%2C%20who%20is%20the%20CEO%20of%20a%20wealth%20management%20software%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Ecompany.%20He%20is%20based%20in%20North%20Carolina.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20his%20employment.%20This%20piece%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20single%20brilliant%20decision%20might%20create%20wealth.%20But%20the%20best%20way%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F5-kinds-of-capital-that-can-save-generational-wealth-advisor-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ekeep%20your%20wealth%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20100%20years%20is%20not%20one%20brilliant%20decision%2C%20but%20hundreds%20of%20good%20decisions%20over%20many%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20more%20than%2030%20years%20working%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-the-2025-family-office-boom-shaping-the-worlds-superrich-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eultra-high-net-worth%20families%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20including%20most%20recently%20as%20CEO%20of%20Eton%20Solutions%20%E2%80%94%20I've%20seen%20this%20pattern%20firsthand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20successful%20families%20tend%20to%20share%20these%20four%20habits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b6762717-bbaf-4ee3-9f02-1d60e6babbc1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECreating%20the%20right%20family%20culture%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiggest-mistakes-billionaire-families-make-wealth-transfer-succession-inheritance-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emost%20successful%20families%3C%2Fa%3E%20instil%20a%20sense%20of%20purpose%20in%20the%20next%20generations.%20They%20foster%20an%20environment%20where%20the%20children%20and%20grandchildren%20don't%20feel%20entitled%2C%20but%20are%20motivated%20to%20make%20their%20own%20way%20and%20add%20value%20to%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20these%20families%2C%20the%20subsequent%20generations%20don't%20see%20the%20wealth%20as%20their%20own%2C%20but%20as%20something%20they%20steward%20for%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20all%20of%20our%20clients%20do%20a%20really%20great%20job%20with%20that.%20I'm%20often%20amazed%20at%20how%20successful%20the%20second%20and%20third%20generations%20are%20in%20building%20their%20own%20careers%20and%20achieving%20something%20in%20their%20lives%2C%20despite%20not%20needing%20to%20because%20they%20already%20have%20more%20than%20enough%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229dee9477-2015-4202-87d7-51de38eaa28b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETreating%20tax%20planning%20as%20an%20ongoing%20process%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20biggest%20thing%20these%20families%20do%20to%20maintain%20their%20wealth%20is%20being%20very%20intentional%20and%20thoughtful%20about%20expenses%20and%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETypically%2C%20one%20of%20the%20highest%20costs%20in%20these%20situations%20is%20taxes%2C%20and%20how%20you%20invest%20your%20money%20can%20be%20either%20incredibly%20tax-efficient%20or%20incredibly%20tax-inefficient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20you%20could%20buy%20an%20equity%20fund%20where%20the%20manager%20is%20buying%20and%20selling%20all%20the%20time.%20You'd%20expect%20a%20significant%20proportion%20of%20short-term%20capital%20gains%20to%20be%20taxed%20each%20year%2C%20reducing%20the%20client's%20net%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20alternative%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ftaxes%2Ftax-loss-harvesting%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etax-loss%20harvesting%20strategy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20you%20buy%20a%20basket%20of%20stocks%20rather%20than%20a%20mutual%20fund%20and%20sell%20positions%20at%20a%20loss%20to%20offset%20gains%20elsewhere.%20The%20gross%20return%20expectation%20is%20the%20same%2C%20but%20the%20after-tax%20returns%20are%20significantly%20higher.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20wealthy%20families%20spend%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20hiring%20people%20to%20ensure%20they're%20not%20making%20tax-inefficient%20decisions.%20They%20don't%20treat%20tax%20planning%20as%20a%20one-time%20exercise%20but%20as%20an%20ongoing%20process%20that%20considers%20every%20financial%20decision%20from%20all%20perspectives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222bdfeab6-ec8a-415b-bebf-24a95c4095eb%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EInvesting%20long-term%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20common%20behavior%20is%20buying%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-build-wealth-lessons-entrepreneurs-millionaires-financial-independence-interviews-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eholding%20core%20assets%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20long%20periods%20to%20reduce%20taxes%20and%20transaction%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20if%20they%20bought%20a%20house%20in%20Aspen%20and%20held%20onto%20it%20for%20decades%2C%20the%20asset's%20appreciation%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20significant%20and%20outweigh%20the%20cost%20of%20maintaining%20it%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20principle%20applies%20to%20financial%20assets.%20Ultra-high-net-worth%20individuals%20with%20well-planned%20equity%20portfolios%20almost%20never%20pay%20taxes%20on%20them%20because%20they%20buy%20and%20hold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%2C%20for%20example%2C%20they%20need%20%241%20million%20to%20buy%20real%20estate%2C%20they%20won't%20sell%20investments%20and%20incur%20taxes.%20Instead%2C%20they'll%20borrow%20against%20their%20portfolio%20or%20take%20out%20a%20mortgage.%20Very%20wealthy%20people%20tend%20to%20avoid%20paying%20cash%20for%20their%20homes%20because%20it's%20not%20the%20smartest%20way%20to%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e4ae2ded-c9bd-4e0b-8c1f-27b32b7f1150%5C%22%3EBeing%20frugal%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20may%20be%20surprised%2C%20but%20ultra-high-net-worth%20individuals%20can%20be%20very%20frugal.%20While%20most%20people%20assume%20that%20they%20wouldn't%20worry%20about%20the%20nitty-gritty%20stuff%20if%20they%20had%20that%20much%20money%2C%20I%20think%20one%20way%20people%20retain%20their%20wealth%20is%20by%20being%20very%20frugal%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmultimillionaire-balance-frugality-treating-kids-indulging-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epaying%20attention%20to%20costs.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20that%20can%20go%20to%20extremes.%20I%20could%20give%20you%20several%20examples%20of%20people%20worth%20over%20%24100%20million%20asking%20one%20of%20their%20advisors%20to%20look%20into%20a%20cost%20worth%20less%20than%20%2410.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20right%20way%20to%20approach%20things%20is%20to%20be%20consistently%20intentional%20about%20all%20your%20financial%20decisions%2C%20and%20it's%20how%20wealthy%20families%20stay%20wealthy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fultrarich-families-4-habits-preserve-generational-wealth-tips-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1778925361000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a0455f958810e27922ad16c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fultrarich-families-4-habits-preserve-generational-wealth-tips-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20CEO%20of%20a%20wealth%20management%20software%20company%20said%20hundreds%20of%20good%20decisions%20over%20many%20years%20is%20what%20preserves%20riches.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jzitser%40businessinsider.com%20(Joshua%