2C%20but%20she's%20been%20able%20to%20keep%20the%20family%20afloat.%20Her%20words%20have%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20so%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrandparents-raising-grandchildren-aging-retirement-caregiving-custody-housing-financial-struggles-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrandparents%20raising%20grandchildren%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20system%20is%20failing%20us.%20I%20don't%20need%20support%20for%20myself%20%E2%80%94%20I%20survived%20fine%20on%20my%20own%20%E2%80%94%20but%20when%20you%20have%20two%20teenage%20boys%2C%20they%20need%20assistance.%20There's%20no%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrandparents-raising-grandchildren-parenting-retirement-financial-hardship-caregiving-aging-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esafety%20net%20for%20grandparents%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20especially%20for%20those%20without%20legal%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20five%20children%2C%20whom%20I%20raised%20mostly%20on%20my%20own%2C%20and%2017%20grandchildren.%20I%20have%20my%20two%20grandsons%20because%20their%20parents%20were%20unable%20to%20care%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20son%20is%20the%20father%20of%20the%20boys%20and%20is%2047%20now.%20I've%20had%20Jason%20and%20Blaze%20throughout%20their%20lives.%20A%20few%20times%20when%20they%20were%20younger%2C%20the%20court%20gave%20me%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fraising-grandchildren-caregiving-parenting-financial-struggles-retirement-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etemporary%20custody%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20their%20parents%20were%20unable%20to%20raise%20them.%20I've%20been%20that%20stronghold%20and%20safety%20net%20to%20catch%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20wants%20to%20hear%20from%20grandparents%20%3Cstrong%3Ecaring%20for%20their%20grandchildren%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20and%20older%20Americans%20caring%20for%20younger%20loved%20ones.%20%3Cstrong%3EShare%20your%20story%20by%20filling%20out%20this%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSc3B3DqRcKUfGoxcUcf_oEPQOwyzJf0I-jL15r4T_XT_ZOs1Q%2Fviewform%3Fusp%3Dpreview%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Equick%20form%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dc31a1e7-8a8e-46e3-98fd-0700a3772b13%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20son%20hasn't%20signed%20the%20papers%20to%20give%20me%20legal%20custody%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20my%20son%20were%20to%20walk%20in%20and%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20them%20with%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20can%20walk%20out%20of%20here%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20can't%20afford%20an%20attorney%20to%20go%20through%20the%20system%3B%20the%20last%20one%20I%20tried%20to%20get%20wanted%20%24800%20upfront.%20Still%2C%20the%20school%20let%20me%20enroll%20them%20because%20the%20district%20knows%20the%20parents'%20history.%20I've%20been%20able%20to%20get%20medical%20care%20for%20them%2C%20and%20they're%20on%20my%20tax%20forms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESomeone%20told%20me%20to%20try%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foldest-kid-foster-siblings-big-family-pros-cons-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efoster%20care%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20it's%20a%20road%20I%20refuse%20to%20go%20down.%20I%20don't%20trust%20the%20system.%20It%20would%20hurt%20me%20so%20badly%20to%20know%20that%20I%20let%20my%20grandchildren%20go%20into%20foster%20care%20because%20I%20couldn't%20afford%20to%20feed%20or%20house%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b6575081-9798-423d-89d3-fe09883907e7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI've%20tried%20to%20apply%20for%20food%20stamps%2C%20but%20they%20tell%20me%20I%20make%20too%20much%20money%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20earn%20%2440%2C000%20a%20year%20as%20a%20facilities%20manager%20at%20a%20building.%20I'd%20need%20to%20make%20half%20of%20that%20to%20qualify.%20The%20boys%20have%20an%20older%20sister%20who%20gets%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-needed-snap-benefits-laid-off-postpartum-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efood%20stamps%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20sometimes%20buys%20groceries%20for%20us.%20Our%20church%20contributes%20food%20from%20the%20pantry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20in%20a%20two-bedroom%20apartment%2C%20with%20Jason%20sleeping%20in%20the%20living%20room%2C%20but%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20purchase%20a%20small%20house.%20They%20now%20have%20their%20own%20bedrooms.%20Our%20lights%20and%20water%20have%20never%20been%20turned%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faffordable-vehicles-disappearing-american-car-market-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecar%20note%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20mortgage%20notes%2C%20and%20other%20bills%20to%20pay.%20I'd%20like%20to%20be%20able%20to%20give%20the%20boys%20more.%20It%20hurts%20me%20that%20we%20go%20out%20to%20dinner%20only%20maybe%20once%20a%20month%2C%20and%20that's%20a%20big%20expense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225736f9a1-c126-4c44-b674-a966c83c1e86%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20can't%20give%20them%20things%20that%20other%20kids%20get%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20love%20to%20take%20them%20to%20Disney%20World%20or%20on%20a%20cruise%2C%20but%20I%20can't%20afford%20it.%20They're%20aware%20of%20our%20financial%20situation%20and%20that%20we%20can't%20do%20a%20lot%20of%20things%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20want%20them%20to%20worry.%20They%20know%20that%20I%20don't%20have%20the%20financial%20means%20to%20put%20them%20through%20college%2C%20so%20I'm%20hoping%20they%20can%20secure%20scholarships.%20I%20won't%20let%20them%20do%20nothing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey're%20good%20boys%20and%20don't%20do%20things%20that%20difficult%20teenagers%20do%2C%20other%20than%20not%20cleaning%20their%20rooms.%20Sometimes%2C%20I%20have%20to%20crack%20down%20more%20and%20say%20no.%20Jason%20wasn't%20doing%20well%20in%20Spanish%2C%20so%20I%20took%20his%20phone%20away%20to%20make%20him%20aware%20of%20the%20consequences.%20That%20hurt%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20time%2C%20he%20broke%20his%20phone.%20I%20could%20have%20purchased%20him%20a%20new%20phone%20immediately%2C%20but%20I%20knew%20he%20had%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fletting-adult-kids-make-mistakes-parenting-lesson-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elearn%20a%20lesson%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20took%20me%20a%20few%20months%20to%20replace%20his%20phone%20because%20I%20needed%20him%20to%20have%20some%20form%20of%20reliable%20communication.%20This%20isn't%20what%20a%20grandmother%20should%20have%20to%20do%3B%20it's%20a%20parent's%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221d4bda5f-c5b2-4489-b959-4c11a1fd60fd%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20have%20arthritis%2C%20so%20I%20can't%20do%20all%20the%20things%20that%20parents%20can%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20had%20both%20knees%20replaced%2C%20and%20I'm%20a%20little%20slow%20getting%20around.%20I'm%20up%20at%205%20a.m.%20to%20get%20the%20boys%20ready%2C%20and%20I%20have%20to%20be%20at%20work%20by%207.%20I%20work%20until%203%2C%20and%20the%20boys%20come%20home%20and%20do%20some%20housework.%20Sunday%20is%20my%20day.%20I%20go%20to%20church%2C%20and%20in%20the%20afternoons%2C%20I%20cook%20and%20relax.%20I%20feel%20like%20I'm%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flife-after-basic-income-more-savings-working-two-jobs-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efalling%20short%3C%2Fa%3E%20sometimes%20as%20a%20parent%20because%20I%20don't%20have%20the%20time%20or%20energy%20to%20cook%20a%20full%20meal%20during%20the%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBlaze%20works%20a%20job%20on%20Fridays%20and%20Saturdays.%20It's%20not%20a%20lot%20of%20money%2C%20but%20it%20helps%20and%20builds%20character.%20They're%20not%20driving%20my%20car%20because%20I%20can't%20afford%20the%20insurance%2C%20so%20I%20pick%20him%20up%20at%209%20or%2010%20at%20night%20when%20he%20gets%20off.%20The%20younger%20one%20wants%20to%20work%20too%2C%20but%20I%20can't%20carpool%20two%20kids%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cc9ec3f6-f53e-4f80-9f83-651f37fc2abd%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20do%20try%20to%20be%20their%20grandmother%20more%20than%20I%20get%20to%20be%20a%20parent%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20parent%20by%20providing%20them%20with%20a%20shelter%20over%20their%20head%2C%20food%2C%20and%20clothing%2C%20but%20I'm%20a%20grandmother%20by%20being%20able%20to%20spoil%20them%20when%20I%20can.%20My%20other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-goes-vacation-twice-year-grandparents-pick-up-the-tab-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrandchildren%20come%20to%20visit%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20call%20me%2C%20and%20I%20try%20to%20spoil%20them%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20boys%20are%20closer%20to%20their%20mom%20than%20to%20their%20dad.%20I%20try%20to%20have%20them%20maintain%20contact.%20I%20try%20to%20give%20them%20confidence%20to%20not%20feel%20sorry%20about%20what%20they%20went%20through%3B%20I%20don't%20want%20them%20to%20use%20their%20circumstances%20as%20a%20crutch.%20If%20they%20make%20good%20decisions%2C%20they're%20going%20to%20have%20good%20outcomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worry%20about%20what%20would%20happen%20if%20something%20happens%20to%20me.%20Will%20they%20be%20able%20to%20support%20themselves%20and%20be%20independent%3F%20I'm%20sure%20some%20family%20would%20assist.%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20see%20them%20get%20angry%20and%20go%20into%20the%20foster%20care%20system%20and%20decide%20to%20turn%20to%20drugs%20or%20drinking.%20They%20may%20have%20to%20work%20a%20little%20harder%20to%20get%20to%20where%20they%20want%20to%20be%2C%20but%20they'll%20get%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20love%20them%20to%20death%2C%20and%20all%20I%20can%20do%20is%20give%20them%20love.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrandparents-raising-grandchildren-cant-retire-aging-financial-insecurity-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1778922721000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a072d7dabc4e9d88574a684%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrandparents-raising-grandchildren-cant-retire-aging-financial-insecurity-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Carol%20Leonard%2C%20a%2065-year-old%20grandmother%20in%20Baton%20Rouge%2C%20raises%20her%20grandsons%20alone%2C%20facing%20financial%20challenges%20without%20legal%20custody%20support.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nsheidlower%40businessinsider.com%20(Noah%20Sheidlower)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20was%20rejected%20for%20a%20job%206%20minutes%20after%20I%20applied.%20I%20told%20the%20company%20that%20AI%20was%20screening%20out%20strong%20candidates.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221257%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Man%20sitting%20on%20a%20couch%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a04c2e7abc4e9d8857493d7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22943%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIT%20professional%20Tony%20Tellez%20of%20Indianapolis%20said%20he%20was%20rejected%20for%20a%20job%20a%20few%20minutes%20after%20he%20submitted%20his%20application%20on%20a%20Sunday%20night.%3Cp%3ETony%20Tellez%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETony%20Tellez%2C%2049%2C%20recently%20launched%20a%20job%20search%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%2010%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20near-instant%20rejection%20from%20an%20employer%20convinced%20the%20IT%20pro%20that%20he%20wasn't%20given%20a%20fair%20chance.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETellez%20said%20he%20told%20the%20company's%20HR%20chief%20that%20AI%20was%20filtering%20out%20qualified%20candidates.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Tony%20Tellez%2C%20a%2049-year-old%20IT%20professional%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3Ebased%20in%20Indianapolis.%20This%20story%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20my%20career%20at%20the%20entry%20level%20and%20worked%20my%20way%20up%20to%20essentially%20running%20IT%20companies%20in%20the%20managed-services%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Espace%2C%20overseeing%20IT%20operations%20for%20multiple%20clients.%20Recently%2C%20I%20found%20myself%20on%20the%20job%20market%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%2010%20years.%20It's%20changed%20a%20lot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20some%20interviews%20right%20away%2C%20but%20I%20also%20got%20a%20lot%20of%20rejections.%20Nobody%20likes%20to%20be%20rejected.%20I've%20got%20children%2C%20rent%2C%20and%20animals%20to%20take%20care%20of%2C%20and%20those%20responsibilities%20start%20to%20weigh%20on%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20Sunday%20night%2C%20my%20frustrations%20reached%20a%20breaking%20point.%20I%20had%20applied%20for%20a%20senior%20position%20at%20a%20managed-services%20firm%20that%20I%20was%20more%20than%20qualified%20for%20around%2011%3A15%20p.m.%20About%20six%20minutes%20later%2C%20I%20received%20an%20email%20that%20simply%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20declined%20your%20application.%26quot%3B%20The%20company%20didn't%20even%20provide%20a%20reason%20like%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe're%20pursuing%20other%20candidates.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20didn't%20make%20any%20sense.%20I%20applied%20at%20a%20time%20when%20no%20one%20was%20likely%20to%20be%20manually%20reviewing%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20and%20rejecting%20them.%20I%20reread%20the%20job%20listing%2C%20and%20it%20clearly%20said%20that%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%20%E2%80%94%20something%20I%20don't%20have%20%E2%80%94%20was%20preferred%20but%20not%20required.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EAlso%2C%20my%20best%20friend%20is%20an%20HR%20consultant%2C%20and%20she%20made%20sure%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20included%20all%20the%20necessary%20keywords.%20I%20even%20ran%20it%20through%20an%20open-source%20applicant-tracking%20system%20to%20check%20that%20it%20was%20well-optimized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20after%20I%20saw%20that%20rejection%20email%20come%20in%2C%20I%20went%20to%20the%20company's%20LinkedIn%20page%2C%20found%20their%20HR%20director%2C%20and%20sent%20him%20this%20message.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EHi%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EI%20just%20applied%20for%20your%20Service%20Desk%20Manager%20role%2C%20and%20was%20immediately%20rejected.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EI%20have%2017%20years%20of%20continued%20growth%20and%20improvement%20in%20the%20IT%20space%20including%20the%20healthcare%20space%20and%20a%20lab%20environment.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EMy%20last%20six%20years%20have%20been%20in%20service%20delivery%20and%20operations%20management.%20I%20am%20highly%20qualified%20for%20this%20role%2C%20but%20the%20AI%20that%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%20uses%20is%20kicking%20me%20back%20within%20minutes%20of%20my%20application%20because%20I%20do%20not%20have%20a%20Bachelors%20degree.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EJust%20a%20heads%20up%2C%20you%20are%20missing%20out%20on%20highly%20qualified%20candidates%20because%20of%20a%20reliance%20on%20AI%2C%20and%20while%20I%20agree%20AI%20has%20its%20place%20in%20our%20space%2C%20I%20believe%20I%20am%20proof%20of%20its%20failure.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EI%20simply%20would%20ask%20you%20to%20review%20my%20resume%20and%20credentials%20manually%20in%20order%20to%20better%20evaluate%20my%20candidacy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cem%3EThank%20you%20for%20your%20time.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EI%20sent%20it%20partly%20because%20it's%20already%20frustrating%20for%20someone%20to%20lose%20a%20job%20and%20have%20to%20search%20for%20a%20new%20one.%20It's%20even%20worse%20when%20you%20have%20to%20deal%20with%20rejection%20from%20a%20robot.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EAnother%20reason%20is%20that%20I've%20developed%20and%20deployed%20applicant%20tracking%20systems%2C%20so%20I%20understand%20what%20it%20takes%20to%20configure%20them%20properly.%20There's%20a%20problem%20here%2C%20and%20the%20company's%20leadership%20may%20not%20know%20that%20they're%20potentially%20missing%20out%20on%20quality%20candidates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20haven't%20heard%20anything%20back%2C%20and%20I%20probably%20won't.%20The%20job%20listing%20is%20no%20longer%20up%2C%20so%20I%20don't%20know%20if%20it%20was%20filled.%20I%20just%20know%20that%20I'm%20not%20ready%20to%20retire%20anytime%20soon.%20I%20love%20working.%20I%20love%20fixing%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20since%20used%20AI%20to%20make%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmistakes-job-seekers-avoid-using-ai-resumes-cover-letters-networking-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Er%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20more%20AI-friendly%3C%2Fa%3E.%20You've%20got%20to%20fight%20fire%20with%20fire.%20However%2C%20I've%20also%20started%20targeting%20companies%20that%20say%20in%20their%20job%20listings%20that%20every%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20submitted%20is%20reviewed%20by%20a%20human.%20In%20some%20of%20my%20past%20jobs%2C%20I%20was%20responsible%20for%20hiring%20people%2C%20and%20I%20prided%20myself%20on%20reading%20every%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20that%20came%20in.%20It's%20crazy%20how%20much%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-hired-job-search-white-collar-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ejob%20market%20has%20changed%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fit-pro-reached-out-after-receiving-job-rejection-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1778922721000%